  <name>HexChat</name>
  <summary>IRC Client</summary>
  <description>
    <p>HexChat is an IRC client based on XChat, but unlike XChat it's completely free for both Windows and Unix-like systems.</p>
    <p>Since XChat is open source, it's perfectly legal. For more info see the XChat FAQ. It is also completely free for any use including commercial.</p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Python and Perl scripting support</li>
      <li>Plugin support for C and other languages</li>
      <li>Spell checking (with auto replacement and auto-learn dictionaries)</li>
      <li>Multiple server/channel windows for one process</li>
      <li>Spell checking (with auto replacement and auto-learn dictionaries)</li>
      <li>Customizable look and feel (themes)</li>
      <li>Auto-logging, auto-away, auto-identify</li>
      <li>DCC file transfer with passive mode and IPv6 support</li>
      <li>SSL/TLS connections</li>
      <li>Proxy support (HTTP/SOCKS4/SOCKS5)</li>
      <li>Auto-join channels on invite</li>
      <li>Auto-reconnect with delay</li>
      <li>Open URLs with a single click</li>
      <li>Colored nicklist</li>
      <li>Customizable command aliases</li>
      <li>Advanced ignore system</li>
      <li>Spell checking (with auto replacement and auto-learn dictionaries)</li>
      <li>And much more!</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
